“I am the perfect example of manifestation.”
When @ojasrajani said this, the room went silent.
From Bollywood’s glam rooms to owning her truth as a proud trans woman, she manifested a life that once didn’t even seem possible.
This isn’t just a story—it’s a masterclass in courage.

Watch the full reel to feel the power of showing up as your whole self.
Tag someone who needs this reminder today.

Ready to manifest your boldest life? Start here.
Hit save, share, and follow for more stories of South Asian firestarters. 

#ManifestationStory #OjasRajani #TheGirlNextDoorPodcast #DesiVoices #LGBTQIndia #SouthAsianStories #TransPower #BollywoodMakeupArtist #DesiPodcast #InspiringWomen #PrideAndPower #BrownGirlMagic #QueerAndProud #RepresentationMatters #manifestyourdreams #manifest #trending #amritbela

“Trans. Not a Trap.”
When makeup artist & icon Ojas Rajani opens up about the real myths South Asians believe about trans women, it’s time we listen.
She shares a shocking yet all-too-common story of love, rejection, and the dangerous assumptions people make about gender and desire.

It’s not just a reel, it’s a reality check.
Let’s bust the stereotypes and start seeing people for who they truly are not who we assume they should be.

Tag someone who needs to unlearn this.
Watch till the end & share your thoughts below.
